<item>
            <title>[OAK-3333] SplitOperations purges _commitRoot entries too eagerly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-3333</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-2528&quot; title=&quot;Entries in _commitRoot not purged&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-2528&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-2528&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; introduced purging of _commitRoot entries without associated local changes on the document. Those _commitRoot entries are created when a child nodes is added and the _children flag is touched on the parent.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The purge operation is too eager and removes all such entries, which may result in an undetected hierarchy conflict.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
